FBIS3-9482 "dreeu058_i_94012" FBIS-EEU-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Attacks Continue in Bihac, Cazin Regions AU2503103994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 25 Mar 94 AU2503103994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Report by Mirza Sadikovic] [Text] The activities of the Serbian aggressor in Bihac district continued throughout the day yesterday. [Words indistinct] the Bihac part of the front and the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau were under constant attacks from mortars and antiaircraft arms. In the zone of responsibility of the General Staff of the Croatian Defense Council of the region, the terrorist [words indistinct] especially in (Pljesavica) part and in the part of [word indistinct]. They have been attacking the Bihac and Cazin districts at irregular intervals so far. On the separating lines with the paramilitary formations of the so-called Velika Kladusa autonomists [words indistinct]. In its bestial mission, the Abdic's army last night continued to destroy and set fire to residential and other kinds of installations in [word indistinct] regions, Krivaja, Zdenkovici, Selimovici, Bocici, and (Hadzici). Beside the attacks that lasted throughout the night, which were substantially assisted by the chetniks, regrouping has been noted in the area of Liskovac and Stulici and we therefore expect new attacks and [words indistinct]. According to incomplete reports, some 200 families have been exiled from these areas. The situation in the district is increasingly more difficult. The promised corridor via (Petrov Licki Dol) still has not been opened, the humanitarian situation is also growing increasingly more difficult, and the spring sowing is also in question [words indistinct].
